Field.Name: Rigid
Field.Description: Used for conductors that are made of solid material.

Field.Name: Stranded
Field.Description: Used for conductors that are made of multiple individual strands (used for most automotive cores).

Field.Name: Foil
Field.Description: Used for conductors that are a foil (e.g. some shields).

Field.Name: Braided
Field.Description: Used for conductors that are made of multiple individual strands that are braided together (often used for shields).

Field.Name: Other
Field.Description: ThePrimaryPartType"Other" is used for parts that are described by a direct instance ofPartOrUsageRelatedSpecification. These are parts that do not have a specific classification in the VEC and can be described with aPartOrUsageRelatedSpecificationandCustomProperties.The correspondingRoleis theSpecificRole.

Field.Name: PartStructure
Field.Description: ThePrimaryPartType"PartStructure" has an inconsistency with VEC conventions for historical reasons, which is kept for backwards compatibility. The correspondingPartOrUsageRelatedSpecificationis thePartStructureSpecification.However, the correspondingRoleis thePartWithSubComponentsRole.

UADataType.Documentation: Abstract base class for extendable elements. Extendable elements have the possibility to define non-standard custom properties.

The bounding box is defined for the processed state of the component, as it appears in the finished product. Therefore, it is valid to use the bounding box as simplified geometry of the component for viewing or simple DMU operations. For correct 3D positioning, the bounding might require a transformation in the coordinate system of the component (seeLocalGeometrySpecification.BoundingBoxPositioning).

The bounding box defines the smallest cuboid (box) that can contain a described part completely. If a component has multiple variants, the bounding box is the smallest cuboid that can contain every variant, while maintaining the spatial orientation of the bounding box and component variants.

It is valid to use theBoundingBoxto describe the dimensions of a component, even if not all dimensions are known (e.g. only length and width). However, it must be possible to transform such a partial bounding box into a complete bounding box by adding the missing dimensions.

Field.Name: X
Field.Description: Defines the extent of the bounding box in the direction of x(length).

Field.Name: Y
Field.Description: Defines the extent of the bounding box in the direction of y(width).

Field.Name: Z
Field.Description: Defines the extent of the bounding box in the direction ofz(height).

UADataType.Documentation: Abstract base class for all elements which can be configured with a VariantConfiguration.

A contact point defines the relationship between Terminals, Seals, Plugs, Cavities and Wires. It specifies a single contacting variant. This means that the contacting is manufactured, as specified by theContactPoint. Either all participants (Cavities, Terminals, Seals, Wires) set into a relationship by theContactPointexist in a specific harness or none. There is no requirement, to filter the participants of a contacting situation with information derived from VariantConfigurations or assembly / module associations in order to create a manufacturing variant.

TheContactPointrepresents a single potential. Consequently, all cavities and wires referencing / being referenced by aContactPointare short-circuited and have the same potential (even if the signals on the wires are named differently. If a contacting of a terminal has more than one potential (e.g. a coax-contact) one contact point for each potential is needed.

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: Specifies a unique identification of the ContactPoint. The identification is guaranteed to be unique within the ContactingSpecification.

Field.Name: MountedTerminal
Field.Description: References the terminal that is used for contacting defined by the ContactPoint.

Field.Name: WireMounting
Field.Description: Specifies the WireMouting defined by ContactPoint. More than one WireMounting is allowed in order to support variance. In concrete configuration the WireMounting with all referenced elements present is used.

UADataType.Documentation: An OccurrenceOrUsage is an abstract appearance of a part in the harness. This can either be a concrete part (with a part number or something similar) or the description (specification / requirements) of a part that should be used at that position. In the first case it would be a PartOccurrence in the second case a PartUsage.

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: Specifies a unique identification of theOccurrenceOrUsage. The identification is guaranteed to be unique within the context. For all VEC-documents anOccurrenceOrUsage-instance can be trusted to be the same if the context-instance is the same and the identification of theOccurrenceOrUsageis the same.

Field.Name: Role
Field.Description: Specifies the different roles of the OccurrenceOrUsage.

UADataType.Documentation: A PartOccurrence is an instance of a component with a specified part number (PartVersion).

Field.Name: Part
Field.Description: References the PartVersion that is instantiated by this PartOccurrence.

UADataType.Documentation: A RoutableElement is an element that can be routed, which mean it is possible to assign it to a Path in the Topology.
A WireElementReference represents the usage of a WireElement in the context of a PartUsage or PartOccurrence. For contacting purposes, a WireElementReference has WireEnds. KBLFRM-384

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: Specifies a unique identification of the WireElementReference. The identification is guaranteed to be unique within the WireRole.

Field.Name: ReferencedWireElement
Field.Description: References the WireElement that is represented by the WireElementReference.

Field.Name: WireEnd
Field.Description: Specifies the ends of the WireElementReference for contacting purposes.

Field.Name: WireLength
Field.Description: Specifies the different length of a wire.

UADataType.Documentation: Abstract base class for the definition ofCrimpDetail-information. SeeCoreCrimpDetail& InsulationCrimpDetail.

Field.Name: Size
Field.Description: Defines the expected size of the crimp. Theheightis measured in direction of the crimp opening. Thewidthis measured in orthogonal to theheightand orthogonal to main axis of the terminal (TerminalSpecification.OverallLength).

UADataType.Documentation: TheCoreCrimpDetaildefines crimp values for a conductor crimp (wire crimp). The selection criteria to which theCoreCrimpDetailapplies are defined by the referencedConductorSpecification.

Field.Name: InsulationCrimpDetails
Field.Description: Defines the differentInsulationCrimpDetailsthat are valid combinations for thisCoreCrimpDetail.

Field.Name: PullOffForce
Field.Description: The minimum force that the completed crimp (core crimp only, insulation crimp non-functional) should withstand when wire is being pulled off the terminal. Above that force, the crimp can be expected to be destroyed at any time.

UADataType.Documentation: TheInsulationCrimpDetaildefines crimp values for a insulation crimp. The selection criteria to which theInsulationCrimpDetailapplies are defined by the referencedInsulationSpecificationand theConductorSpecificationreferenced by the containingCoreCrimpDetail.

Field.Name: PullOffForce
Field.Description: The minimum force that the completed crimp should withstand when wire is being pulled off the terminal. Above that force, the crimp can be expected to be destroyed at any time.

UADataType.Documentation: Abstract super-class for physical objects (e.g. a Terminal), virtual objects (e.g. a 150% Harness) as well as documents (e.g. a wiring diagram). In difference to AP 212 the VEC makes it only possible to describe/exchange information about Versions since Master-Objects cannot exist without one or more Versions.

Field.Name: CompanyName
Field.Description: Defines the publishing company of the ItemVersion. The companyName is part of the main identifier of an ItemVersion together with the corresponding number (partNumber or documentNumber) and version (partVersion or documentVersion).

UADataType.Documentation: ADocumentVersionis a unique identifier for a piece of information in a company context. The DocumentVersion is one of the three anchors for PDM information in the VEC. All technical information about a PartVersion is contained in one or more documents. The documents are containing the actual content of the VEC since all Specifications are an element of a document.

Field.Name: DocumentNumber
Field.Description: The documentNumber is the major identifier of a DocumentVersion. The format is user defined and respectively company specific.

Field.Name: DocumentVersion
Field.Description: The documentVersion specifies the version index of a document (see also documentNumber).

Field.Name: DigitalRepresentationIndex
Field.Description:
An arbitrary change index that indicates if the digital representation (the content in VEC) of thisDocumentVersionhas been changed / regenerated. This can be for example an index, a timestamp or a checksum. This allows the detection of changes in the content, even when the DocumentNumber & DocumentVersion is the same.

For a more detailed explanation in the context see "Parts & Documents". KBLFRM-837.

Field.Name: Specification
Field.Description: Specifies the Specifications contained in the DocumentVersion. All structured, technical information in the VEC is described by such Specifications.

UADataType.Documentation: APartVersionis unique identifier for a part in a company context. A part can be any components within a vehicle. The PartVersion is one of the three anchors for PDM information in the VEC. All technical information about a PartVersion is contained in one or more documents. These describing elements are normally referencing to the PartVersion.

Field.Name: PartNumber
Field.Description: The partNumber is the major identifier of a PartVersion. The format is user defined and respectively company specific. For all VEC-documents a PartVersion-instance can be trusted to be identical if the combination of partNumber, partVersion and companyName is identical.

UADataType.Documentation: AResourceVersionis unique identifier for a resource in a company context. Resources are elements used to produce, handle or service a harness, e.g. tools or machines, that do not end up in the product (seePartVersion). TheResourceVersionis one of the three anchors for PDM information in the VEC.

Field.Name: ResourceNumber
Field.Description: TheResourceNumberis the major identifier of aResourceVersion. The format is user defined and respectively company specific. For all VEC-documents aResourceVersion-instancecan be trusted to be identical if the combination ofResourceNumber,ResourceVersionandCompanyNameis identical.

Field.Name: ResourceVersion
Field.Description: TheResourceVersionspecifies the version index of a resource (see alsoResourceNumber).

UADataType.Documentation: A Role is the corresponding mechanism for OccurrenceOrUsages to the PartOrUsageRelatedSpecifcations for PartVersions or PartUsages. The PartOrUsageRelatedSpecifcations are describing a certain aspect of the master data of a part. A Role describes the corresponding properties and relationships for instances of a part (e.g. the usage specific properties of a wire occurrence like the length or the contacting).

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: Specifies a unique identification of the Role. The identification is guaranteed to be unique within the OccurrenceOrUsage.

UADataType.Documentation: A CavitySealRole defines the instance specific properties and relationships of a cavity seal.

Field.Name: CavitySealSpecification
Field.Description: References theCavitySealSpecificationthat is instanced by thisCavitySealRole.

UADataType.Documentation: A TerminalRole defines the instance specific properties and relationships of a terminal.

Field.Name: TerminalSpecification
Field.Description: References theTerminalSpecificationthat is instanced by thisTerminalRole.

Field.Name: WireReceptionReference
Field.Description: Specifies theWireReceptionReferencesof thisTerminalRole.

UADataType.Documentation: A PluggableTerminalRole defines the instance specific properties and relationships of a pluggable terminal.
A WireRole defines the instance specific properties and relationships of a wire.

Field.Name: WireSpecification
Field.Description: References theWireSpecificationthat is instanced by thisWireRole.

Field.Name: WireElementReference
Field.Description: Specifies the WireElementReferences used in the WireRole. For multi core wires more than one WireElementReference is needed.

UADataType.Documentation: Abstract super-class for all specifications. Every technical information exchanged with the VEC is contained in the different specializations of a specification.

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: Specifies a unique identification of the specification. The identification is guaranteed to be unique within the document containing the specification. For all VEC-documents a Specification-instance can be trusted to be identical if the DocumentVersion-instance is the same (see DocumentVersion) and the identification of the Specification is the same.

UADataType.Documentation: The CompositionSpecificiation is used to define a set of occurrences required to describe unambiguously the design of a composite part. This does not have to be necessarily the same occurrences which are building the bill of material. Example: A company might want to regard an antenna cable as one part out of a bill of material perspective. However, at the same time it may be useful for the company to be able to describe the contacting of the antenna cable within the VEC. (see also PartStructureSpecification)

Field.Name: Component
Field.Description: Specifies the PartOccurrences defined in the CompositionSpecification.

UADataType.Documentation: Specification for the definition of conducting properties of a WireElement.

Field.Name: CrossSectionArea
Field.Description: Specifies the cross-section area of the conductor (e.g. 0,5 mm²). The cross-section area is a nominal value, which refers to the conducting properties of the conductor normalized to the properties of a full material core.

Field.Name: Type
Field.Description: Specifies the type of the conductor, e.g. if it is rigid or stranded.

UADataType.Documentation: Defines the properties of a circular conductor (core) which are specific for them.

Field.Name: OutsideDiameter
Field.Description: Specifies the outside diameter of the core.

UADataType.Documentation: Specification for the description of the contacting. A contacting defines the relationships between Terminals, Seals, Plugs, Cavities and Wires.

Field.Name: ContactPoint
Field.Description: Specifies the ContactPoints defined by the ContactingSpecification.

UADataType.Documentation: Specification for the definition of insulation properties of a WireElement.

Field.Name: BaseColor
Field.Description: Specifies the base color of the insulation.

Field.Name: FirstIdentificationColor
Field.Description: Specifies the first identification color of the insulation.

Field.Name: SecondIdentificationColor
Field.Description: Specifies the second identification color of the insulation.

Field.Name: Thickness
Field.Description: Specifies the thickness of the insulation.

UADataType.Documentation: Base class for all specifications which are describing aPartVersionor aPartUsage. APartOrUsageRelatedSpecificationspecifies a certain aspect of the described part or usage (e.g. general technical part information, connector housing aspects or wire aspects).

Field.Name: SpecialPartType
Field.Description: The specialPartType allows the specification of subclassifications for a PartOrUsageRelatedSpecification (e.g. different types of connector housings).

Field.Name: DescribedPart
Field.Description: References the PartVersion(s) to which the information defined in this specification applies. Example: If the PartOrUsageRelatedSpecification is a GeneralTechnicalPartSpecifcation and it defines that the color is "green" then all PartVersion referenced by this association are "green".

UADataType.Documentation: TheCavityPartSpecificationis an abstract class for common properties of non-electrical parts that are used inCavities.
Specification for the definition of cavity seals. ACavitySealis a watertight non-electrical object to fill a populated Cavity.
Specification for the definition of common properties for technical parts.

Field.Name: ColorInformation
Field.Description: Specifies the color of the part.

Field.Name: BoundingBox
Field.Description: Defines the bounding box of the part.

UADataType.Documentation: Specification for the definition of terminals. A terminal can own multiple WireReceptions & TerminalReceptions.

Field.Name: ConnectionALength
Field.Description: Specifies the length of the terminal between the contact area (terminal reception) and the crimp are (wire reception, see diagram "Terminal Dimensions").

Field.Name: OverallLength
Field.Description: Specifies the overall length the terminal (see diagram "Terminal Dimensions").

Field.Name: WireReception
Field.Description: Specifies the WireReceptions of the terminal described by the TerminalSpecification.

UADataType.Documentation: Specification for the definition of pluggable terminals.

Specification for the definition of a wire. This can either be a complex multicore wire or a normal single core. In the VEC a wire is defined by one WireElement, which may be composed from other WireElements.

Field.Name: WireElement
Field.Description: Specifies theWireElementthat represents the root of theWireSpecification.

UADataType.Documentation: A WireElementSpecification is the basic element to describe a wire in the VEC. A WireElementSpecification can be atomic or composed recursively out of other WireElementSpecifications. A WireElementSpecification can reference an InsulationSpecification, if it has an insulation, a CoreSpecification, if it has a core or a WireGroupSpecification if it is a grouping of other WireElementSpecifications in the Wire (e.g. a multi-core wire with twisted pairs).

Field.Name: OutsideDiameter
Field.Description: Specifies the outside diameter of the WireElement.

Field.Name: ConductorSpecification
Field.Description: If theWireElementhas a core then the specification of the core is referenced here.

Field.Name: InsulationSpecification
Field.Description: If theWireElementhas an insulation then the specification of the insulation is referenced here.

UADataType.Documentation: Specification for the definition of wire receptions. A WireReception is the area of a terminal where the contacting with a wire element (e.g. by crimping) takes place.

Field.Name: InsulationDisplacementLength
Field.Description: Specifies the length of the insulation which must be stripped off to fit to this wire reception.

Field.Name: ConductorCrimpLength
Field.Description: Specifies the length of the conductor crimp (wire reception, see diagram "Terminal Dimensions").

Field.Name: CrimpConnectionLength
Field.Description: Specifies the length of the crimp area, conductor + insulation crimp (wire reception, see diagram "Terminal Dimensions").

Field.Name: InsulationCrimpLength
Field.Description: Specifies the length of the insulation crimp (wire reception, see diagram "Terminal Dimensions").

Field.Name: WireTipProtrusion
Field.Description: Defines the valid length range in which the protrusion of the conductor from the conductor crimp must be located.

Field.Name: CoreCrimpDetails
Field.Description: Defines theCrimpDetailsfor this WireReception.

Field.Name: CrimpBarrelType
Field.Description: When the crimp barrel is open, the wire can be laid into the terminal from above. If the crimp barrel is closed, the wire must be fed in from the front.

UADataType.Documentation:
ATolerancedefines the permissible limit or limits of variation for defined values (e.g. aNumericalValue). The tolerated value is defined by the context in which theToleranceis contained / used.

The values of the limits of theTolerance,LowerBoundaryandUpperBoundary, shall be interpreted as "modifiers" to the actual value. To obtain an absolute range of valid values, the values of boundaries shall be added to the actual value, regardless of theUpperorLowerprefix. For example, to define a value of 100mm with a tolerated variation between 95mm and 105mm, the definition would beValue= 100 mm,LowerBoundary=-5, UpperBoundary=+5. TheUnitof theToleranceboundaries is always the same as in the defining context.

Field.Name: LowerBoundary
Field.Description: Specifies the lower boundary for the tolerance.

Field.Name: UpperBoundary
Field.Description: Specifies the upper boundary for the tolerance.

UADataType.Documentation: AWireElementspecifies aWireElementSpecificationin the context of aWireSpecification. This is necessary to define a uniqueidentificationof aWireElementSpecificationin the context of aWireSpecification.Additionally, theWireElementserves as anchor for the instancing of a wire (WireElementReference) as theWireElementSpecificationsare not uniquely related to aWireSpecificationfor reasons of reusability.

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: The identification of the WireElement. The identification is guaranteed to be unique within a wire and immutable. The identification is guaranteed to be the same for the same WireElement over different VEC documents.

Field.Name: WireElementSpecification
Field.Description: Reference theWireElementSpecificationthat is represented by theWireElement.

Field.Name: SubWireElement
Field.Description: Defines thesubWireElementsof thisWireElement. ThesubWireElementsshall be consistent with thesubWireElementSpecificationsof theWireElementSpecificationreferenced by thisWireElementand shall resemble that hierarchy.

UADataType.Documentation: A WireEnd is the end of a wire. This class mainly needed for the definition of a contacting. As a wire can be contacted on more than two ends (e.g. IDC) the WireEnd has a position on the wire.

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: Specifies a unique identification of the WireEnd. The identification is guaranteed to be unique within the WireElementReference.

Field.Name: PositionOnWire
Field.Description:
Specifies the order of theWireEndson theWireElementReference. This must be a value between 0 and 1. ThePositionOnWireis defined as a floating point number, to allow the ordering of an arbitrary number ofWireEndswhile having constant known values for the first and lastWireEnd("0.0" & "1.0"). ThePositionOnWireisnotdefined as a relative factor with respect to theWireLengthto determine an exact position of theWireEndon the wire. This would not be defined unambiguously, since aWireElementReferencecan define multiple lengths of differentWireLengthTypes. If such an interpretation can be made, it is tool or process specific definition.

In case ofWireRolewith multipleWireElementReferencesthe ordering of theWireEndsshall be consistent for allWireElementReferences.That means that allWireEndswithPositionOnWire = 0.0are on the same side of theWireRole.

Field.Name: StrippingLength
Field.Description: Defines the length by which an insulation on this stripped relative to thisWireEnd,defined by thecutBackLength. E.g. acutBackLengthof 20mm and astrippingLengthof 10mm means, that thisWireElementReferenceis cutback by 20mm relative to length of whole wire, on the side of the definingWireEnd.Form the remainingWireElementReferenceare then 10mm insulation removed.

Field.Name: InsulationPullbackLength
Field.Description: Defines a partial stripping process in which the insulation is pulled back by the insulationPullbackLength after being cut at the strippingLength, and is left on the WireEnd e.g. for logistic reasons. The insulationPullbackLength must be shorter than the strippingLength; otherwise, it would not qualify as partial stripping.

UADataType.Documentation: AWireMountingdefines the mounting of a wire end to terminal. If the contacting is required to be waterproof a cavity seal can be mounted additionally.

Field.Name: MountedCavitySeal
Field.Description: References the cavity seal that is used for the wire mounting.

Field.Name: ReferencedWireEnd
Field.Description:
References the wire ends that are used for the wire mounting. The minimum cardinality is one, because a wire mounting without wire end makes no sense.

The maximum cardinality is * in order to support multi crimps.

Field.Name: WireMountingDetail
Field.Description: Specifies the WireMoutingDetails, if a detailed description of the relationships between WireEnds and WireReceptions is needed.

UADataType.Documentation:
With a WireMountingDetail it is possible to describe a detailed wire mounting.

This is needed if the information which wire end is mounted onto which wire reception is important (e.g. coax contacts).

Field.Name: CoreCrimpSize
Field.Description: Defines the required core crimp size (width & height) of this specific wire mounting situation.

Field.Name: InsulationCrimpSize
Field.Description: Defines the required insulation crimp size (width & height) of this specific wire mounting situation.

Field.Name: WireTipProtrusion
Field.Description: Defines the valid length range in which the protrusion of the conductor from the conductor crimp must be located.

Field.Name: ContactedWireReception
Field.Description: References the WireReception that is used for the WireMounting.

Field.Name: ReferencedWireEnd
Field.Description: References the WireEnds that are mounted to referenced WireReception. A cardinality of more than one is allowed in order support parallel connectors, where multiple wire ends are placed on one side of the connector (one wire reception) and the other wire ends are placed on the other side of the connector (the other wire reception).

Field.Name: AbsoluteSealPosition
Field.Description: The absoluteSealPosition defines distance between the conductor tip and edge of the CavitySeal facing the conductor tip.

Field.Name: CorePullOffForce
Field.Description: The minimum force that the completed crimp (core crimp only, insulation crimp non-functional) should withstand when wire is being pulled off the terminal. Above that force, the crimp can be expected to be destroyed at any time.

UADataType.Documentation: A WireReception is the area of a terminal where the contacting with a wire element (e.g. by crimping) takes place. This class represents such an area on the terminal. Its description is done with a WireReceptionSpecification, which is independent from the TerminalSpecification. This allows the reuse of the specification of similar WireReception on different terminals.

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: Specifies a unique identification of the WireReception. The identification is guaranteed to be unique within the TerminalSpecification (this might be for example a reception number).

Field.Name: Rotation
Field.Description: Defines the rotation of aWireReceptionrelative to theTerminalReception.The rotation of theWireReceptionis the angle between the normal vector on base plane of the crimp area and the y-axis, which is a rotation around the z-axis (right hand rule, compare illustration in"Terminal Coordinate System").

Field.Name: WireReceptionSpecification
Field.Description: References the WireReceptionSpecification that specifies the WireReception.

UADataType.Documentation: AWireReceptionReferenceis an instance of aWireReception.

Field.Name: Identification
Field.Description: Specifies a uniqueidentificationof theWireReceptionReference. Theidentificationis guaranteed to be unique within theTerminalRole(this might be for example a reception number).

Field.Name: WireReception
Field.Description: References theWireReceptionthat is instanced by thisWireReceptionReference.

UADataType.Documentation: Allows the definition of material information. Attributes of the type Material normally have the multiplicity [0..*]. This means that such an attribute can have material values for differentreferenceSystems. It must not have multiple values for the samereferenceSystems.

Field.Name: Key
Field.Description: The key of the material in the corresponding material reference system.

Field.Name: ReferenceSystem
Field.Description: The identification of the material reference system, which is defining possible values and the semantic of material keys.

UADataType.Documentation: Defines the size of an element by width & height. Per definition is width > height.

Field.Name: Width
Field.Description: The width of the element.

Field.Name: Height
Field.Description: The height of the element.

UADataType.Documentation: Abstract class either for a single numerical measure or a range of numerical measures with upper, lower, or upper and lower bounds.

Field.Name: UnitComponent
Field.Description: References the unit of the value.

UADataType.Documentation: A quantity expressed with a numerical value and a unit.

Field.Name: ValueComponent
Field.Description: Specifies the value of the numerical value.

Field.Name: Tolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance for the dimension.

UADataType.Documentation: A pair of numerical values representing a value range.

Field.Name: Minimum
Field.Description: Lower bound of the value range.

Field.Name: Maximum
Field.Description: Upper bound of the value range.
